Welcome to the November 1995 issue of the GAC FLAK!

This issue uses only fonts from the PageStream3 release with the
exception of HelvNrw-Bold (which came with later versions of
PageStream3 but which some of you might not have. It is available from
Soft-Logik Publishing for a nominal fee.).

There is a news release from Be, Inc. concerning their new platform; the
first part of an interview with Jay Minor; an IRC with Gilles Bourdin;
info on new software; and a submission for for the upcoming GAC PAK.

William F. Maddock
Editor in Chief
GAC FLAK
The Newsletter of the Gateway Amiga Club, Inc.

